    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A further evolution of 16th and 17th century Old-Flemish lace. The motifs are mostly flowers, vines or animals and often encircled with decorative thread.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
